title: Audrey Nuna - Cellulite (2023)
description: Audrey Nuna's "Cellulite" music video, directed by Zac Dov, is a vivid narrative of self-liberation and defiance, drawing inspiration from icons like the Pharcyde and Missy Elliott. The video visually represents Nuna's personal theme of overcoming constraints, symbolized by motifs of flying and motion, reflecting her introspective yet rebellious spirit. It's a cinematic portrayal of cutting out life's "toxic fat," aiming to resonate with viewers on a journey of spiritual unburdening.

title: Usher, H.E.R. - Risk It All (2024)
description: In the 2024 music video 'Risk It All' directed by Dave Meyers, Usher and H.E.R. deliver an emotionally charged performance, underscored by contemporary dance, on a rotating platform in a dimly lit setting. The video, known for its sophisticated yet steamy ambiance, culminates in a poignant moment with Usher tearfully singing the final note. This collaboration is a standout part of 'The Color Purple' soundtrack, showcasing the artistic depth and vulnerability of both artists.

title: A$AP Ferg - Floor Seats (2019)
description: In the music video for "Floor Seats," A$AP Ferg gives a supposedly VIP tour of New York City on his Redline BMX, showcasing the rare and unique experience of his life—complete with gravity-defying bike tricks and a closing act of a house party that makes Harlem look like the ultimate VIP lounge. Because nothing says VIP like riding a BMX through the streets and ending the night with a raucous house bash, right?

title: Vince Staples - Norf Norf (2015)
description: The music video for "Norf Norf" by Vince Staples, released in 2015, features documentary-style footage that portrays the harsh realities of life in North Long Beach, California. Through scenes of Vince in a police car and visuals of his neighborhood, the video underscores the song's themes of systemic injustice and police brutality.

French Cassettes - White Noise (2024)
description: The music video for "White Noise" by French Cassettes, released in 2024, visually encapsulates themes of love, heartache, and self-discovery. It portrays the emotional complexities of relationships through a narrative of emotional turbulence and introspection, reflecting the aftermath of love and loss. The video enhances the song's lyrical exploration of finding solace amid emotional turmoil, using vibrant and expressive imagery to convey the depth of these experiences.

title: Ken Carson - Fighting My Demons (2023)
description: The music video for "Fighting My Demons" by Ken Carson, directed by Cole Bennett, was released in 2023 and features unique, glitchy visuals. The video presents a series of grainy, 3D footage that gives off the impression of being shot with night-vision goggles, offering a surreal viewing experience. It mainly showcases Ken Carson partying and performing his lyrics, creating a montage that aligns with the song's themes. The video's eerie and dark aesthetics were noted for drawing inspiration from the style of 1990s Japanese cinema, culminating in a profound, existential moment where Ken faces a haunting black void, adding depth and narrative to the visual experience.

An accompanying music video was released, featuring a zoetrope-inspired CG animation style.
